30template <class T, int size = 256>
31class Predicate {
32 public:
33 inline Predicate() = default;
34 inline bool get(uchar c);
35
36 private:
37 friend class Test;
38 bool CalculateValue(uchar c);
39 class CacheEntry {
40 public:
41 inline CacheEntry()
42 : bit_field_(CodePointField::encode(0) | ValueField::encode(0)) {}
43 inline CacheEntry(uchar code_point, bool value)
44 : bit_field_(
45 CodePointField::encode(CodePointField::kMask & code_point) |
46 ValueField::encode(value)) {
47 DCHECK_IMPLIES((CodePointField::kMask & code_point) != code_point,
48 code_point == static_cast<uchar>(-1));
49 }
50
51 uchar code_point() const { return CodePointField::decode(bit_field_); }
52 bool value() const { return ValueField::decode(bit_field_); }
53
54 private:
55 using CodePointField = v8::base::BitField<uchar, 0, 21>;
56 using ValueField = v8::base::BitField<bool, 21, 1>;
57
58 uint32_t bit_field_;
59 };
60 static const int kSize = size;
61 static const int kMask = kSize - 1;
62 CacheEntry entries_[kSize];
63};

65// A cache used in case conversion. It caches the value for characters
66// that either have no mapping or map to a single character independent
67// of context. Characters that map to more than one character or that
68// map differently depending on context are always looked up.
69template <class T, int size = 256>
70class Mapping {
71 public:
72 inline Mapping() = default;
73 inline int get(uchar c, uchar n, uchar* result);
74
75 private:
76 friend class Test;
77 int CalculateValue(uchar c, uchar n, uchar* result);
78 struct CacheEntry {
79 inline CacheEntry() : code_point_(kNoChar), offset_(0) {}
80 inline CacheEntry(uchar code_point, signed offset)
81 : code_point_(code_point), offset_(offset) {}
82 uchar code_point_;
83 signed offset_;
84 static const int kNoChar = (1 << 21) - 1;
85 };
86 static const int kSize = size;
87 static const int kMask = kSize - 1;
88 CacheEntry entries_[kSize];
89};

100class Utf16 {
101 public:
102 static const int kNoPreviousCharacter = -1;
103 static inline bool IsSurrogatePair(int lead, int trail) {
104 return IsLeadSurrogate(lead) && IsTrailSurrogate(trail);
105 }
106 static inline bool IsLeadSurrogate(int code) {
107 return (code & 0x1ffc00) == 0xd800;
108 }
109 static inline bool IsTrailSurrogate(int code) {
110 return (code & 0x1ffc00) == 0xdc00;
111 }
112
113 static inline int CombineSurrogatePair(uchar lead, uchar trail) {
114 return 0x10000 + ((lead & 0x3ff) << 10) + (trail & 0x3ff);
115 }
116 static const uchar kMaxNonSurrogateCharCode = 0xffff;
117 // Encoding a single UTF-16 code unit will produce 1, 2 or 3 bytes
118 // of UTF-8 data. The special case where the unit is a surrogate
119 // trail produces 1 byte net, because the encoding of the pair is
120 // 4 bytes and the 3 bytes that were used to encode the lead surrogate
121 // can be reclaimed.
122 static const int kMaxExtraUtf8BytesForOneUtf16CodeUnit = 3;
123 // One UTF-16 surrogate is encoded (illegally) as 3 UTF-8 bytes.
124 // The illegality stems from the surrogate not being part of a pair.
125 static const int kUtf8BytesToCodeASurrogate = 3;
126 static inline uint16_t LeadSurrogate(uint32_t char_code) {
127 return 0xd800 + (((char_code - 0x10000) >> 10) & 0x3ff);
128 }
129 static inline uint16_t TrailSurrogate(uint32_t char_code) {
130 return 0xdc00 + (char_code & 0x3ff);
131 }
132 static inline bool HasUnpairedSurrogate(const uint16_t* code_units,
133 size_t length);
134
135 static void ReplaceUnpairedSurrogates(const uint16_t* source_code_units,
136 uint16_t* dest_code_units,
137 size_t length);
138};

140class Latin1 {
141 public:
142 static const uint16_t kMaxChar = 0xff;
143 // Convert the character to Latin-1 case equivalent if possible.
144 static inline uint16_t TryConvertToLatin1(uint16_t c) {
145 switch (c) {
146 // This are equivalent characters in unicode.
147 case 0x39c:
148 case 0x3bc:
149 return 0xb5;
150 // This is an uppercase of a Latin-1 character
151 // outside of Latin-1.
152 case 0x178:
153 return 0xff;
154 }
155 return c;
156 }
157};

159enum class Utf8Variant : uint8_t {
160#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
161 kUtf8, // UTF-8. Decoding an invalid byte sequence or encoding a
162 // surrogate codepoint signals an error.
163 kUtf8NoTrap, // UTF-8. Decoding an invalid byte sequence or encoding a
164 // surrogate codepoint returns null.
165 kWtf8, // WTF-8: like UTF-8, but allows isolated (but not paired)
166 // surrogate codepoints to be encoded and decoded.
167#endif
168 kLossyUtf8, // Lossy UTF-8: Any byte sequence can be decoded without
169 // error, replacing invalid UTF-8 with the replacement
170 // character (U+FFFD). Any sequence of codepoints can be
171 // encoded without error, replacing surrogates with U+FFFD.
172 kLastUtf8Variant = kLossyUtf8
173};

175class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE Utf8 {
176 public:
177 using State = Utf8DfaDecoder::State;
178
179 static inline uchar Length(uchar chr, int previous);
180 static inline unsigned EncodeOneByte(char* out, uint8_t c);
181 static inline unsigned Encode(char* out, uchar c, int previous,
182 bool replace_invalid = false);
183 static uchar CalculateValue(const uint8_t* str, size_t length,
184 size_t* cursor);
185
186 // The unicode replacement character, used to signal invalid unicode
187 // sequences (e.g. an orphan surrogate) when converting to a UTF-8 encoding.
188 static const uchar kBadChar = 0xFFFD;
189 static const uchar kBufferEmpty = 0x0;
190 static const uchar kIncomplete = 0xFFFFFFFC; // any non-valid code point.
191 static const unsigned kMaxEncodedSize = 4;
192 static const unsigned kMaxOneByteChar = 0x7f;
193 static const unsigned kMaxTwoByteChar = 0x7ff;
194 static const unsigned kMaxThreeByteChar = 0xffff;
195 static const unsigned kMaxFourByteChar = 0x1fffff;
196
197 // A single surrogate is coded as a 3 byte UTF-8 sequence, but two together
198 // that match are coded as a 4 byte UTF-8 sequence.
199 static const unsigned kBytesSavedByCombiningSurrogates = 2;
200 static const unsigned kSizeOfUnmatchedSurrogate = 3;
201 // The maximum size a single UTF-16 code unit may take up when encoded as
202 // UTF-8.
203 static const unsigned kMax16BitCodeUnitSize = 3;
204 // The maximum size a single UTF-16 code unit known to be in the range
205 // [0,0xff] may take up when encoded as UTF-8.
206 static const unsigned kMax8BitCodeUnitSize = 2;
207 static inline uchar ValueOf(const uint8_t* str, size_t length,
208 size_t* cursor);
209
210 using Utf8IncrementalBuffer = uint32_t;
211 static inline uchar ValueOfIncremental(const uint8_t** cursor, State* state,
212 Utf8IncrementalBuffer* buffer);
213 static uchar ValueOfIncrementalFinish(State* state);
214
215 // Excludes non-characters from the set of valid code points.
216 static inline bool IsValidCharacter(uchar c);
217
218 // Validate if the input has a valid utf-8 encoding. Unlike JS source code
219 // this validation function will accept any unicode code point, including
220 // kBadChar and BOMs.
221 //
222 // This method checks for:
223 // - valid utf-8 endcoding (e.g. no over-long encodings),
224 // - absence of surrogates,
225 // - valid code point range.
226 static bool ValidateEncoding(const uint8_t* str, size_t length);
227};

229#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
230class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE Wtf8 {
231 public:
232 // Validate that the input has a valid WTF-8 encoding.
233 //
234 // This method checks for:
235 // - valid utf-8 endcoding (e.g. no over-long encodings),
236 // - absence of surrogate pairs,
237 // - valid code point range.
238 //
239 // In terms of the WTF-8 specification (https://simonsapin.github.io/wtf-8/),
240 // this function checks for a valid "generalized UTF-8" sequence, with the
241 // additional constraint that surrogate pairs are not allowed.
242 static bool ValidateEncoding(const uint8_t* str, size_t length);

267// LineTerminator: 'JS_Line_Terminator' in point.properties
268// ES#sec-line-terminators lists exactly 4 code points:
269// LF (U+000A), CR (U+000D), LS(U+2028), PS(U+2029)
270V8_INLINE bool IsLineTerminator(uchar c) {
271 return c == 0x000A || c == 0x000D || c == 0x2028 || c == 0x2029;
272}
273
274V8_INLINE bool IsStringLiteralLineTerminator(uchar c) {
275 return c == 0x000A || c == 0x000D;
276}
